{"text": " It's finally time to harvest some jackfruit. If you guys have been following along, you probably remember that I had this huge jackfruit on my tree, but one morning when I went out to harvest it, I realized that someone had come into my yard and taken it right off of the tree. And while that was super disappointing, fast forward to today, and we now have a whole bunch more fruit on this tree and defense to protect them. So today we finally get to harvest them. When jackfruit are ripe and ready to harvest, you'll know it because they get a really strong, fruity smell coming from them. And so when I came out to the tree today, I knew that there was one ready to harvest. And when you give them a nice squeeze, if they have some give to them like this, that's how you know that this is the one that's ready to be picked. But the point where this jackfruit was growing off of the tree was too high for me to reach from the ground. So to pick this one, we have to climb. Now that I'm up here, all we have to do is go ahead and clip it off of the tree and then be careful to bring it down safely because these are pretty heavy. And just like that, we have our jackfruit. But while I was up there the first time, I realized that there was another fruit that was even more fragrant than the one that we picked already. So I headed back up and eventually I found it. This one right here is borderline overripe, so we're gonna harvest it as well. Just like that, my workout for the day is complete and we have two nice jackfruit. Most of the time, jackfruit need to be cut in order to remove the fruit segments, but the second one that we harvested was so ripe that I was able to rip it open by just using my hands. As you can see, the inside is filled with different segments of fruit. And what you wanna do is just remove those and then take out the seed in the middle and you're ready to enjoy. Then after removing the seed from the middle of the pod, you can go ahead and pop it right in your mouth. These are so sweet and have a flavor that's really similar to juicy fruit gum. If you've never tried jackfruit before, I would highly recommend it. Now I'm gonna finish removing the segments so that I can go ahead and put them in the fridge for later. And until next time, get outside and see what you can find.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 2.24, "text": " It's finally time to harvest some jackfruit.", "tokens": [50364, 467, 311, 2721, 565, 281, 11917, 512, 7109, 33564, 13, 50476], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12772643368547135, "compression_ratio": 1.8935574229691876, "no_speech_prob": 0.024832673370838165}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 2.24, "end": 3.48, "text": " If you guys have been following along,", "tokens": [50476, 759, 291, 1074, 362, 668, 3480, 2051, 11, 50538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12772643368547135, "compression_ratio": 1.8935574229691876, "no_speech_prob": 0.024832673370838165}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 3.48, "end": 5.68, "text": " you probably remember that I had this huge jackfruit", "tokens": [50538, 291, 1391, 1604, 300, 286, 632, 341, 2603, 7109, 33564, 50648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12772643368547135, "compression_ratio": 1.8935574229691876, "no_speech_prob": 0.024832673370838165}, {"id": 3, "seek": 0, "start": 5.68, "end": 8.4, "text": " on my tree, but one morning when I went out to harvest it,", "tokens": [50648, 322, 452, 4230, 11, 457, 472, 2446, 562, 286, 1437, 484, 281, 11917, 309, 11, 50784], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12772643368547135, "compression_ratio": 1.8935574229691876, "no_speech_prob": 0.024832673370838165}, {"id": 4, "seek": 0, "start": 8.4, "end": 10.32, "text": " I realized that someone had come into my yard", "tokens": [50784, 286, 5334, 300, 1580, 632, 808, 666, 452, 11682, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12772643368547135, "compression_ratio": 1.8935574229691876, "no_speech_prob": 0.024832673370838165}, {"id": 5, 